OL,7,FFormer subpostmaster Lee Castleton,
OL,8,Fwho was declared bankrupt after being
OL,9,Fordered to pay #321,000 in Post
OL,10,FOffice's legal fees in a 2006 court
OL,11,Fcase, said it was "shameful" that
OL,12,Fsubpostmasters are still waiting for
OL,13,Ftheir full compensation payments.
OL,15,FCastleton worked night shifts at a
OL,16,Flocal factory to make ends meet, he
OL,17,Fsaid, "It would be nice, when I don't
OL,18,Fhave to think about the Post Office
OL,19,Fanymore, and I can just think about
OL,20,Fthe Castletons."
